Date: Sun, 19 Apr 2026 17:16:38 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] fix(starry/pipe): wake poll_rx when the write end closes

Readers blocked in poll_io on an empty pipe only saw poll_close wakeups;
explicitly wake poll_rx on write-side teardown so EOF is observed promptly.

Made-with: Cursor

diff --git a/os/StarryOS/kernel/src/file/pipe.rs b/os/StarryOS/kernel/src/file/pipe.rs
index 0193b663..9885ec28 100644
--- a/os/StarryOS/kernel/src/file/pipe.rs
+++ b/os/StarryOS/kernel/src/file/pipe.rs
@@ -43,6 +43,10 @@ pub struct Pipe {
 }
 impl Drop for Pipe {
     fn drop(&mut self) {
+        // Closing the write end must unblock readers waiting on an empty buffer.
+        if self.is_write() {
+            self.shared.poll_rx.wake();
+        }
         self.shared.poll_close.wake();
     }
 }
